			<div class="content" id="post-content-4866233">
									

<p>Seeking green lights: yes</p>
<p>Page type: SCP article</p>
<p>Class: Euclid</p>
<p>Elevator pitch: This SCP is a female elf who has the ability to summon items from anywhere in the multi verse. However even though it sounds like X-men syndrome, she can only summon items that she has a complete understanding of how they are made and/or works.<br />
For example she knows how a T-shirt is made so she can summon one, and she knows how a lightbulb is made and works so she can make one. She has a photographic memory that helps her summon objects. The objects come through a multi-universal portal that appears and disappears within the space of 0.2 seconds.<br />
She has a standard - simple humanoid containment cell and has been allowed access to level 01 areas of the facility she is housed in. She is very cooperative with foundation staff, seemingly understanding of why she is locked up. However she has been declared as a threat because the staff cannot say if she is lying or not. Multiple researchers have agreed that she must be monitored and her cell is to be fully checked every two days as well as all actions done by this SCP. The foundation agrees that she is a dangerous scp and should be heavily monitored</p>
<p>Hook/Attention-Grabber: She can summon life forms that she knows the biology of, however no summond-life form has made it out of the portal in one piece, sometimes it may be missing a limb or patch of fur, or it may just be a bloody mess.</p>
<p>She was discovered 1 year ago when foundation staff noticed a sudden surge in gamma radiation in the area. After having onsite personnel in the area for a day, a portal opened up reveling the SCP and an unknown entity behind it. The unknown entity pushed SCP through and closed the portal behind her. She then quickly surrend willingly.<br />
She came from a universe where her race was being hunted and killed. Her race was able to summon items and track each other via a form of telepathy. The limits of this are unknown but the SCP claims that her race frequently traveled the multi verse aided by a machine they used. Researchers have agreed that a small group of mtf should be close by and ready to terminate the SCP if she shows any signs of hostility.</p>

