<p>Heyo followup!</p>
<p><strong>SAND</strong></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><br />
How will you plan to show all of this in the narrative? currently there is only really interviews, but for some of this information it sounds like there would need to be some sort investigation or further tests.- The child wouldn't be able to show much outside of their own experiences.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Regarding your point about how the tree is called to the Foundation's attention. It's true that this is a little lacking. But I think that the foundation would be interested in rumors/tales that allude to a possible SCP entity. Perhaps the investigation department checks the background for names written on the tree and finds a pattern of anti-social behavior among them. Is there something in SCP that could possible help with this point? like a signature for a nefarious group or individual?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Hmm&#8230; I'm still kind of skeptical on this, the Foundation isn't likely (at least not to me), to take a scout tale of all things seriously enough to look further into it. Unless there is some sort evidence to show otherwise, I don't think the Foundation being curious will work.-do note that even if they did look at the tree/camp ground, they're likely not going to see anything immediately off. They would really need to know what they're looking for if they wanted something concrete.</p>
<p>-Perhaps you could work off this subtly a little bit? with it taking a while for the child to convince their parents and furthermore the Foundation that this is something more than a particularly bad camp experience?</p>
<p>That said;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>like a signature for a nefarious group or individual?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>You could go this route if you want to, however you would need to prepared to expand a bit more on the individual responsible for this. Along with showing a bit more on why the tree was created.</p>
<p>Due to my afore mentioned concerns, no-greenlight</p>
<p>If you would like me review this (or any concept) further, then please feel free to send me a PM or ask via IRC. Response times generally range from 2-12 hours over PMs. If your looking for additional critiques/perspectives in general, then I would highly recommend contacting the butterfly squad :)</p>
